'''Zeno Koen Debast''' (born 24 October 2003) is a Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Primeira Liga]] club [[Sporting CP]] and the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]]. Primarily a [[centre-back]], he can also be deployed as a [[defensive midfielder]].

==Club career==
===Anderlecht===
[[File:Zeno Debast 2024 03 30 - RSCA vs Antwerp.jpg|thumb|left|200pxDebast with [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] in 2024.]]

Debast is a youth product of [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]], signing his first contract in October 2019. He made his professional debut on 2 May 2021, in a 2–2 [[Belgian First Division A]] draw against [[Club Brugge]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.soccerway.com/matches/2021/05/02/belgium/pro-league/club-brugge-kv/royal-sporting-club-anderlecht/3496939/|title=Club Brugge vs. Anderlecht|website=Soccerway|date=24 October 2021}}</ref>{{Better source needed|date=June 2024}}

On 11 June 2024, during an interview for ''[[Het Laatste Nieuws]]'', Debast confirmed that he had agreed personal terms to join Portuguese side [[Sporting CP]] from the [[2024–25 Primeira Liga|2024–25 season]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Doms |first=Kjell |date=11 June 2024 |title=Zeno Debast kondigt vertrek bij Anderlecht aan: "Ik speel volgend seizoen voor Sporting Lissabon"|url=https://www.hln.be/anderlecht/zeno-debast-kondigt-vertrek-bij-anderlecht-aan-ik-speel-volgend-seizoen-voor-sporting-lissabon~a8dd9331/|website=[[Het Laatste Nieuws]]|access-date=12 June 2024|language=nl}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|first=Miguel|last=Mendes|title=Debast confirma transferência para o Sporting! |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/debast-confirma-transferencia-para-o-sporting-2024061114314430043|website=[[A Bola]]|date=11 June 2024|access-date=12 June 2024|language=pt}}</ref>

===Sporting CP===
[[File:ZenoDebast.jpg|thumb|right|200px|Debast in a press conference with [[Sporting CP]].]]

On 4 July, Debast signed a five-year contract with [[Primeira Liga]] side [[Sporting CP]], for a fee of [[€]]15.5 million, plus €5.5 million in add-ons, and a 15% sell-on clause in favor of Anderlecht.<ref>{{Cite web |date=4 July 2024 |title=Zeno Debast é Leão |url=https://www.sporting.pt/pt/noticias/futebol/equipa-principal/2024-07-04/zeno-debast-e-leao |access-date=4 July 2024 |publisher=Sporting CP |language=pt-PT}}</ref><ref name=":0">{{Cite web |date=4 July 2024 |title=Sporting oficializa Debast |url=https://www.abola.pt/futebol/noticias/sporting-oficializa-debast-2024070418033018723 |access-date=4 July 2024 |website=[[A Bola]] |language=pt-PT}}</ref>

On 7 August, he made his debut for the club, where he committed two errors, that led to [[FC Porto–Sporting CP rivalry|rivals]] [[FC Porto|Porto]] first and second goals in their 4–3 loss in the [[2024 Supertaça Cândido de Oliveira]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://portugoal.net/club-news/4011-porto-star-in-seven-goal-super-taca-thriller|title=Porto pull off stunning comeback to beat Sporting in seven-goal Super Taça thriller|date=4 August 2024|access-date=4 August 2024|website=PortuGOAL}}</ref> This resulted in him losing his starting spot, however, on 17 September with regular starter [[Eduardo Quaresma]] being sidelined with a knee injury, Debast was entrusted back to the starting eleven, scoring his first goal for the club, and the first goal of his career, by netting a shot from outside the box in Sporting's 2–0 victory over [[LOSC Lille|Lille]] during the inaugural matchday of the newly formatted [[2024–25 UEFA Champions League league phase|Champions League league phase]].<ref>{{cite web |date=17 September 2024 |title=Gyökeres mostrou-se à Europa e Debast fez as pazes com as bancadas |url=https://www.dn.pt/4597849901/gyokeres-mostrou-se-a-europa-e-debast-fez-as-pazes-com-as-bancadas/ |access-date=18 September 2024 |website=[[Diário de Notícias]]|language=pt}}</ref>

==International career==
In September 2022, Debast received his first call-up to the [[Belgium national football team|Belgian senior squad]] for the [[2022–23 UEFA Nations League]] matches against [[Wales national football team|Wales]] and [[Netherlands national football team|Netherlands]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.sportstar.thehindu.com/football/belgium-squad-nations-league-defender-zeno-debast-gets-maiden-call-up/article65899273.ece/|title=Belgium calls up teenage defender Zeno Debast for Nations League|website=Sport Star|access-date=24 June 2024}}</ref> He debuted against the former opponent on 22 September that ended in a 2–1 victory.<ref>{{Cite news|first=First|last=Last|title=Zeno Debast titularisé au sein de la défense des Diables Rouges face au Pays de Galles|trans-title=Zeno Debast started in the Red Devils defense against Wales|url=https://www.lavenir.net/sports/2022/09/22/zeno-debast-titularise-au-sein-de-la-defense-des-diables-rouges-face-au-pays-de-galles-FTLWMVTNFJGGDK2T2Y7UZFX7QQ/|website=[[L'Avenir (Belgian newspaper)|L'Avenir]]|date=22 September 2022|language=fr}}</ref> Debast was also called up to the [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Belgium|Belgium squad]] for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]] on 10 November 2022.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.rbfa.be/en/news/roberto-martinez-selects-26-devils-world-cup |title=Roberto Martinez selects 26 Devils for the World Cup |publisher=[[Royal Belgian Football Association]]|date=10 November 2022}}</ref>

